definition: pleasant-sounding Wu dialect/also written 吳儂軟語|吴侬软语[Wu2 nong2 ruan3 yu3]
John Lennon (1940-1980), English singer, guitarist, and songwriter

sentences.english: Ono released a statement Tuesday night in tribute to Lennon.
sentences.chinese: 小野周二晚上发表的一份声明中赞扬侬。

sentences.english: Nanon carried off the plate with the eggshells.
sentences.chinese: 拿侬把盛蛋壳的盘子端走。

sentences.english: However, up to now, they still respect Nong Zhigao as their hero who led their first ancestors to flee from calamity.
sentences.chinese: 至今他们仍视侬智高为带领始祖逃难的英雄来崇敬。

sentences.english: Nanon was wonder struck at the sight of a green silk dressing-gown, brocaded with gold flowers in an antique design.
sentences.chinese: 一件金线绣花古式图案的绿绸睡衣，把拿侬看呆了。

sentences.english: Lennon, almost incidentally, had one of the best voices in rock.
sentences.chinese: 而列侬，几近是过于巧合，拥有一副唱摇滚的好嗓子。
解释亚格曼侬所面对的选择。

sentences.english: Nanon carried off the plate with the eggshells .
sentences.chinese: 拿侬把盛蛋壳的盘子端走。

sentences.english: Someone like Mr. Cronon can stand up to the pressure.
sentences.chinese: 像克罗侬先生这样的人士有能力顶住压力。

sentences.english: The Zhuang-Dai-Nong ethnic groups have similar yet diversified Hua-po myths.
sentences.chinese: 壮岱侬民族拥有同中有异的花婆神话。

definition: dialectal equivalent of 沒有|没有[mei2 you3]
contraction of 勿要/must not/please don't
(modal final particle similar to 呢[ne5] or 啦[la5])
mile (unit of length equal to 1,609.344 m)/old form of modern 英里[Ying1 li3]
sentence-final particle similar to 了[le5], but carrying a tone of approval
